The paper proposes a memory network for long-term lifelong learning scenario, which involves processing data streams and retaining important information over time. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper also mentions question answering tasks, which falls under the sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL), and a path-finding task, which falls under the sub-category of computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV).
